  "local_port": 44960,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why can't I see views on my Instagram videos?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you can't see the view count on your Instagram videos. Let's consider some possible explanations:\n\n1. Video type:\n   - Instagram Reels and IGTV videos typically display view counts.\n   - Regular feed videos might not always show view counts, depending on Instagram's current algorithm and settings.\n\n2. Time elapsed:\n   - It may take a short period for view counts to appear after posting.\n\n3. Privacy settings:\n   - If your account is set to private, you might not see view counts on your own videos.\n\n4. Technical issues:\n   - There could be a temporary glitch or bug in the Instagram app.\n\n5. Account status:\n   - If your account is new or has been flagged, Instagram might limit certain features.\n\n6. Platform differences:\n   - View counts might display differently on the mobile app versus the web version.\n\n7. Video duration:\n   - Very short videos might not display view counts in some cases.\n\nTo troubleshoot:\n\n1. Check if the issue persists across different videos you've posted.\n2. Try accessing your profile from another device or the web version.\n3. Ensure your app is updated to the latest version.\n4. If the problem continues, you might want to report it to Instagram's support team.\n\nIf you've recently posted a video and don't see views yet, give it some time. If the issue persists across multiple videos, it might be worth investigating further or contacting Instagram support.",
